OpenLumen licensing note

OpenLumen is licensed under GPL-3.0-or-later.

Why GPL-3.0-or-later:
- Aligns with Red Moon (LibreShift/red-moon), which OpenLumen draws lineage from.
- Strong copyleft means any derivative that ships a binary must publish source, which matters for a system-level app that touches root drivers.
- Compatible with F-Droid inclusion policies.

If you want a permissive license carve-out for a specific module, open an issue.
